               <head>Four treatises on spheres and astrology (&amp; 1 Arabic)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111185 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007101548 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009116122">
                  <summary>Collection of five treatises on spheres (kurah) and astronomy; the first (part a) is an unidentified scientific treatise in Arabic (ff. 1v-10v); the remaining four (parts b-e) are in Persian; part e is early and illustrated </summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
               </msContents>
